---
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="How Toolbase handles data: analytics, cookies, browser storage, outbound links, and your rights. Written in plain language."
	lastUpdated="July 3, 2026"
>
	<p>
		Toolbase ("we", "us", "the site") publishes honest reviews, tutorials, and free
		utilities for solopreneurs at <strong>gettoolbase.org</strong>. This policy
		explains what data the site collects, why, and what control you have over it.
		We have tried to write it in plain language rather than legal boilerplate.
	</p>
	<p>
		The short version: Toolbase has no user accounts and no login. We do not sell
		your data. The only information we collect is standard, aggregated analytics
		about how pages are used, and anything you choose to send us by email.
	</p>

	<h2>Who we are</h2>
	<p>
		Toolbase is an independent publication run by a small team. For any
		privacy question, correction, or data request, contact us at
		<a href="mailto:hello@gettoolbase.org">hello@gettoolbase.org</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>What we collect</h2>
	<h3>Analytics data</h3>
	<p>
		We use Google Analytics 4 to understand which articles and tools people find
		useful. It records non-identifying, aggregated information such as pages
		visited, approximate location (city or region, derived from a truncated IP
		address), device type, browser, referring site, and time spent on a page.
		Google Analytics sets cookies to do this. We do not use this data to identify
		you personally, and IP addresses are anonymized. You can read how Google
		handles this data in the
		<a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
	</p>
	<h3>Data stored in your browser (never sent to us)</h3>
	<p>
		Some features save data locally in your own browser and never transmit it to
		our servers. For example, when you highlight text in an article and tap "Save
		quote", that highlight is stored in your browser's local storage on your
		device only. It stays on your machine, we never see it, and clearing your
		browser data removes it.
	</p>
	<h3>Information you send us</h3>
	<p>
		If you email us, we receive your email address and whatever you write. We use
		it only to reply and to keep a record of the conversation. We do not add you to
		any marketing list without your explicit consent.
	</p>
	<p>
		Toolbase does not knowingly collect names, phone numbers, payment details, or
		any other personal information, because the site has no forms, checkout, or
		account system that would ask for them.
	</p>

	<h2>Cookies and how to control them</h2>
	<p>
		Cookies are small files a website stores in your browser. Toolbase uses them in
		two ways:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> set by Google Analytics, as described above.</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Advertising cookies</strong>, if and when we display ads. See the
			advertising section below.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		You can block or delete cookies at any time through your browser settings.
		Doing so will not break the site, though some usage will no longer be counted
		in our analytics. You can also opt out of Google Analytics specifically using
		Google's
		<a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener" target="_blank">opt-out browser add-on</a>.
	</p>

	<h2>Advertising</h2>
	<p>
		Toolbase may display advertising served by third-party networks, including
		Google AdSense. When ads are shown, these networks, including Google as a
		third-party vendor, may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to
		this and other websites.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads
			based on your visits to Toolbase and other sites on the internet.
		</li>
		<li>
			You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
			<a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.
		</li>
		<li>
			You can opt out of many other third-party vendors' use of cookies for
			personalized advertising at
			<a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">aboutads.info/choices</a>.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Outbound and affiliate links</h2>
	<p>
		Articles and tool pages sometimes link to other companies' products. Some of
		these may be affiliate links, meaning we could earn a small commission if you
		sign up through them, at no extra cost to you. This never changes which tools we
		recommend or what we say about them. When you click an outbound link, that
		third party's own privacy policy governs any data they collect.
	</p>

	<h2>Third-party services we rely on</h2>
	<p>
		To run the site we use a small number of reputable providers, each with their
		own privacy practices:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> for usage measurement.</li>
		<li><strong>Our hosting and content-delivery provider</strong>, which keeps standard server access logs (such as IP address and browser type) for security and reliability.</li>
		<li><strong>Google AdSense</strong>, if and when advertising is enabled.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How long we keep data</h2>
	<p>
		Aggregated analytics data is retained according to Google Analytics' standard
		retention settings. Emails you send are kept only as long as needed to handle
		your query and any reasonable follow-up. Data stored in your own browser stays
		until you clear it.
	</p>

	<h2>Your rights</h2>
	<p>
		Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, or
		delete personal data we hold about you, or to object to certain processing.
		Because we hold almost no personal data, most requests concern email
		correspondence. To make a request, email
		<a href="mailto:hello@gettoolbase.org">hello@gettoolbase.org</a> and we will
		respond within a reasonable time. This includes rights under the EU/UK GDPR,
		the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and India's Digital Personal Data
		Protection Act, 2023.
	</p>

	<h2>Children</h2>
	<p>
		Toolbase is intended for adults running or building businesses. It is not
		directed at children, and we do not knowingly collect data from anyone under 16.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
	<p>
		We may update this policy as the site evolves, for example if we add a
		newsletter or enable advertising. When we do, we will change the "last updated"
		date at the top of this page. Significant changes will be noted clearly.
	</p>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>
		Questions about privacy or this policy? Email
		<a href="mailto:hello@gettoolbase.org">hello@gettoolbase.org</a> or visit our
		<a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
